headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 26 points and had 10 assists as the Dallas Mavericks eased to a 130-117 victory over the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Hardaway pace Mavericks to comfortable 130-117 win over Wizards

events.name: New York Knicks at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 24 points, including a pull-up jumper from the top of the lane with 18.8 seconds remaining, and the New York Knicks held on for a 116-114 victory over the Atlanta...
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Brunson lead Knicks to a 116-114 victory over the Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Derrick White scored 14 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter to lead the Boston Celtics to a 117-107 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night in a matchup of the early pacesetters in the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Derrick White, Jayson Tatum lead short-handed Celtics over 76ers in matchup of East leaders

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 37 points and a season-high 13 assists, Malik Beasley scored a season-high 30 points and the Milwaukee Bucks overcame Giannis Antetokounmpo’s absence to beat the Toronto Raptors 128-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 37, Bucks overcome Antetokounmpo's absence to beat Raptors 128-112

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero took four dribbles as he backed into the lane and didn't bother to look at the rim before lifting off for a fadeaway jumper. Moments later, teammates mobbed him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero hits turnaround jumper with 1 second left as Magic beat Bulls 96-94

headlines.description: — Someday soon, the Phoenix Suns hope that their three All-Stars will be on the floor at the same time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 31 in return from injury, Suns roll past Timberwolves 133-115

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 29 points and 16 rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings overcame LeBron James' 108th career triple-double and the Lakers' fourth-quarter comeback bid for their fourth straight victory, 125-110 over Los Angeles on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings overcome LeBron's triple-double, hold on in 4th quarter for 125-110 win over Lakers

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 34 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers handed the Portland Trail Blazers their fifth straight loss with a 109-95 victory on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell has 34 points and Cavaliers end road trip with 109-95 win over Portland
